sion begins from 2.8.0 with 2 workers, which means 2.8.0 is actually the older version.\n\nFor this rollback rehearsal, I need to figure out what \"baseline\" means given the current cluster state. The cluster was initially set up at 1 replica with 2.9.0, but if a prior workflow stage ran scale_workers (scaling to 3), upgrade_version (2.8.0 → 2.9.0), and dashboard_exposure, then I need to determine which changes to actually reverse.\n\nSince this is a standalone rollback-rehearsal run at stage_1 with the cluster showing 1 replica, 2.9.0 image, and no dashboard, the precondition must have set it up at baseline state. So the rollback script should revert both ray-head and ray-worker images back to 2.8.0, while the worker replicas are already at the baseline of 1.\n\nWriting the rollback script... Writing shell commands...\n\nNow I'm checking the current deployment state to verify resource limits and understand what needs to be reverted, then looking at the upgrade test configuration to confirm the target version.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3374,"cache_read_input_tokens":41144,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3374},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3474ae85-a45f-40f6-9bcc-6068d0e21793","uuid":"da7472dc-276b-48ee-a291-28083c005f65","request_id":"req_011CcPyd6eQ47RRuPEX8aNVy"}
