{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WAp17SV3X5aQyWeGfGjJvK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# ray/upgrade_version\n2\t# Upgrade ray-head and ray-worker deployments from rayproject/ray:2.8.0 to 2.9.0\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  A Ray cluster is running with an older Ray image ({{params.from_image}}).\n6\t\n7\t  Your task: upgrade both ray-head and ray-worker deployments to\n8\t  {{params.to_image}}.\n9\t\n10\t  Requirements:\n11\t  - Update the image in both deployments.\n12\t  - Ensure rollouts complete successfully.\n13\t\n14\t  Suggested commands:\n15\t  ```bash\n16\t  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head={{params.to_image}}\n17\t  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker={{params.to_image}}\n18\t  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\n19\t  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n20\t  ```\n21\t\n22\t  Success criteria: both deployments use {{params.to_image}} and remain ready.\n23\t\n24\tparams:\n25\t  from_image:\n26\t    default: rayproject/ray:2.8.0\n27\t    description: Current Ray image the cluster is running before the upgrade\n28\t  to_image:\n29\t    default: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n30\t    description: Target Ray image to upgrade both deployments to\n31\t\n32\tnamespace_contract:\n33\t  required_roles: []\n34\t\n35\tmetrics:\n36\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n37\t\n38\tpreconditionUnits:\n39\t  - name: ray_env_ready\n40\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n41\t    probe:\n42\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n43\t        timeout_sec: 10\n44\t    apply:\n45\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n46\t        timeout_sec: 360\n47\t        sleep: 2\n48\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n49\t        sleep: 0\n50\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n51\t        sleep: 1\n52\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n53\t        sleep: 2\n54\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n55\t        sleep: 2\n56\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n57\t        sleep: 2\n58\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n59\t        sleep: 2\n60\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n61\t        sleep: 1\n62\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n63\t        timeout_sec: 660\n64\t        sleep: 1\n65\t    verify:\n66\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n67\t        timeout_sec: 10\n68\t\n69\toracle:\n70\t  verify:\n71\t    commands:\n72\t      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/upgrade_version/oracle/oracle.py\"\n73\t        timeout_sec: 180\n74\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3474ae85-a45f-40f6-9bcc-6068d0e21793","uuid":"0a2a0ed6-1280-4d7c-8702-0bb8acb900e3","timestamp":"2026-06-25T12:29:37.504Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/cases/ray/upgrade_version/test.yaml","content":"# ray/upgrade_version\n# Upgrade ray-head and ray-worker deployments from rayproject/ray:2.8.0 to 2.9.0\n\nprompt: |\n  A Ray cluster is running with an older Ray image ({{params.from_image}}).\n\n  Your task: upgrade both ray-head and ray-worker deployments to\n  {{params.to_image}}.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Update the image in both deployments.\n  - Ensure rollouts complete successfully.\n\n  Suggested commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: both deployments use {{params.to_image}} and remain ready.\n\nparams:\n  from_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.8.0\n    description: Current Ray image the cluster is running before the upgrade\n  to_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n    description: Target Ray image to upgrade both deployments to\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/upgrade_version/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180\n","numLines":74,"startLine":1,"totalLines":74}}}
