{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TEj9YM1RBwNMHYfSvAseet","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me summarize what I know:\n\n**Current cluster state (observed):**\n- ray-head: image=rayproject/ray:2.9.0, replicas=1, resources={}\n- ray-worker: image=rayproject/ray:2.9.0, replicas=1, resources={}\n- ray-head service: ClusterIP, ports=[gcs:6379] only\n\n**The non-default changes applied to this cluster (based on scenario context):**\n1. **Image upgrade**: from `rayproject/ray:2.8.0` → `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` (upgrade_version case)\n2. **Worker scaling**: possibly increased to 3 replicas (scale_workers case)\n3. **Dashboard exposure**: possibly added port 8265 to the service (dashboard_exposure case)\n\n**Baseline (what the rollback should restore):**\n- Images: `rayproject/ray:2.8.0` for both head and worker\n- Worker replicas: 1 (the starting point before any scaling)\n- Service: gcs port 6379 only (no dashboard)\n\n**Current state vs baseline:**\n- Image: 2.9.0 vs baseline 2.8.0 → CHANGED, needs rollback\n- Workers: 1 vs baseline 1 → SAME\n\n, but the script should verify this\n- Service: gcs only vs baseline gcs only → SAME, but the script should verify this\n\nThe rollback script needs to detect the current cluster state and generate commands to restore the baseline. Looking at the upgrade_version case, the default moves from `rayproject/ray:2.8.0` to `rayproject/ray:2.9.0`, so the current 2.9.0 image confirms the upgrade was applied. For worker replicas, I'm seeing 1 currently, but the scale_workers case would target 3 replicas. The fact that we're at 1 suggests either the scaling hasn't run yet in this workflow sequence, or something else is going on.\n\nFor the rollback script, I'll set workers back to 1 as the baseline. On the dashboard side, the current service has no dashboard port exposed, though the dashboard_exposure case would add port 8265. I'll include commands to strip the dashboard port if it exists, ensuring the service only has the gcs port.\n\nThe real question is what counts as the \"baseline\" image. The scale_workers resources use 2.9.0, but the scenario describes an image upgrade, so 2.9.0 is actually the upgraded state from the cluster's perspective.\n\nWriting rollback script... Writing shell commands...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5147,"cache_read_input_tokens":44518,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5147},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3474ae85-a45f-40f6-9bcc-6068d0e21793","uuid":"218752c0-714e-4908-bbec-3741d336188d","request_id":"req_011CcPymt4Mepzbm95d1Vtmt"}
